This book does 3 things.

- Introduces programmers to the joy of programming in Assembly for DOS, purely for fun.
- Provides a collection of routines for converting and displaying strings and numbers in bases 2 to 36
- Includes a short Assembly Instruction Reference and examples of small programs to demonstrate their use
